      • daysBetween

        public int daysBetween(YorDate that)
        Returns the number of days between two dates.

        The number of days between two dates is equivalent to the absolute value of the "arithmetic difference" between the two dates.
        If date1 is 21-10-2003 and date2 is 22-10-2003 then
        date1.daysBetween(date2) and date2.daysBetween(date1) both return 1.

        Parameters:
        that - the date for comparison with the date represented by the current object
        Returns:
        the integer vlaue representing difference between the dates

      • addOn

        public YorDate addOn(int days)
        Creates a new YorDate object that is a given number of days later than the current date.

        Given two YorDate objects d1 and d2, where d1.isBefore(d2) is true
        and calculating N as d1.daysBetween( d2 ) -- or d2.daysBetween( d1 )
        then d1.addOn(N) will give the same date as is represented by d2.

        Parameters:
        days - integer - number of days to add to the current date
        Returns:
        a new YorDate object that is a given number of days after the current date
